{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":643,"text":"Once upon a time,"},{"time":3535,"text":"there was a place called Lesterland."},{"time":6975,"text":"Now Lesterland looks a lot like the United States."},{"time":9930,"text":"Like the United States, it has about 311 million people,"},{"time":14667,"text":"and of that 311 million people,"},{"time":17005,"text":"it turns out 144,000 are called Lester."},{"time":21888,"text":"If Matt's in the audience,"},{"time":23016,"text":"I just borrowed that, I'll return it in a second,"},{"time":25706,"text":"this character from your series."},{"time":28371,"text":"So 144,000 are called Lester,"},{"time":30794,"text":"which means about .05 percent is named Lester."},{"time":35074,"text":"Now, Lesters in Lesterland have this extraordinary power."},{"time":38802,"text":"There are two elections every election cycle in Lesterland."},{"time":41965,"text":"One is called the general election."},{"time":44178,"text":"The other is called the Lester election."},{"time":47519,"text":"And in the general election, it's the citizens who get to vote,"},{"time":50504,"text":"but in the Lester election, it's the Lesters who get to vote."},{"time":53776,"text":"And here's the trick."},{"time":54910,"text":"In order to run in the general election,"},{"time":58561,"text":"you must do extremely well"},{"time":61107,"text":"in the Lester election."},{"time":62480,"text":"You don't necessarily have to win, but you must do extremely well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":65581,"text":"Now, what can we say about democracy in Lesterland?"},{"time":69531,"text":"What we can say, number one,"},{"time":70924,"text":"as the Supreme Court said in Citizens United,"},{"time":73560,"text":"that people have the ultimate influence over elected officials,"},{"time":77838,"text":"because, after all, there is a general election,"},{"time":80486,"text":"but only after the Lesters have had their way"},{"time":83438,"text":"with the candidates who wish to run in the general election."},{"time":86940,"text":"And number two, obviously, this dependence upon the Lesters"},{"time":90543,"text":"is going to produce a subtle, understated,"},{"time":93305,"text":"we could say camouflaged, bending"},{"time":95734,"text":"to keep the Lesters happy."},{"time":98925,"text":"Okay, so we have a democracy, no doubt,"},{"time":102194,"text":"but it's dependent upon the Lesters"},{"time":103870,"text":"and dependent upon the people."},{"time":105880,"text":"It has competing dependencies,"},{"time":108522,"text":"we could say conflicting dependencies,"},{"time":110932,"text":"depending upon who the Lesters are."},{"time":115202,"text":"Okay. That's Lesterland."}]},{"cues":[{"time":117546,"text":"Now there are three things I want you to see now that I've described Lesterland."},{"time":120305,"text":"Number one, the United States is Lesterland."},{"time":123546,"text":"The United States is Lesterland."},{"time":125422,"text":"The United States also looks like this, also has two elections,"},{"time":127803,"text":"one we called the general election,"},{"time":130942,"text":"the second we should call the money election."},{"time":134186,"text":"In the general election, it's the citizens who get to vote,"},{"time":136352,"text":"if you're over 18, in some states if you have an ID."},{"time":138946,"text":"In the money election, it's the funders who get to vote,"},{"time":142162,"text":"the funders who get to vote, and just like in Lesterland,"},{"time":144922,"text":"the trick is, to run in the general election,"},{"time":147081,"text":"you must do extremely well in the money election."},{"time":149901,"text":"You don't necessarily have to win. There is Jerry Brown."},{"time":152522,"text":"But you must do extremely well."},{"time":155074,"text":"And here's the key: There are just as few relevant funders"},{"time":159602,"text":"in USA-land as there are Lesters in Lesterland."}]},{"cues":[{"time":165091,"text":"Now you say, really?"},{"time":166995,"text":"Really .05 percent?"},{"time":170138,"text":"Well, here are the numbers from 2010:"},{"time":172354,"text":".26 percent of America"},{"time":174650,"text":"gave 200 dollars or more to any federal candidate,"},{"time":177386,"text":".05 percent gave the maximum amount to any federal candidate,"},{"time":181850,"text":".01 percent -- the one percent of the one percent --"},{"time":185282,"text":"gave 10,000 dollars or more to federal candidates,"},{"time":188490,"text":"and in this election cycle, my favorite statistic"},{"time":191566,"text":"is .000042 percent"},{"time":195421,"text":"— for those of you doing the numbers, you know that's 132 Americans —"},{"time":199458,"text":"gave 60 percent of the Super PAC money spent"},{"time":203418,"text":"in the cycle we have just seen ending."},{"time":206168,"text":"So I'm just a lawyer, I look at this range of numbers,"},{"time":208898,"text":"and I say it's fair for me to say"},{"time":210607,"text":"it's .05 percent who are our relevant funders in America."},{"time":214858,"text":"In this sense, the funders are our Lesters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218160,"text":"Now, what can we say about this democracy in USA-land?"},{"time":221660,"text":"Well, as the Supreme Court said in Citizens United,"},{"time":224002,"text":"we could say, of course the people have the ultimate influence"},{"time":226839,"text":"over the elected officials. We have a general election,"},{"time":230868,"text":"but only after the funders have had their way"},{"time":234077,"text":"with the candidates who wish to run in that general election."},{"time":238240,"text":"And number two, obviously,"},{"time":240763,"text":"this dependence upon the funders"},{"time":243035,"text":"produces a subtle, understated, camouflaged bending"},{"time":246967,"text":"to keep the funders happy."},{"time":249604,"text":"Candidates for Congress and members of Congress"},{"time":252648,"text":"spend between 30 and 70 percent of their time"},{"time":256931,"text":"raising money to get back to Congress"},{"time":259107,"text":"or to get their party back into power,"},{"time":260882,"text":"and the question we need to ask is, what does it do to them,"},{"time":264307,"text":"these humans, as they spend their time"},{"time":266424,"text":"behind the telephone, calling people they've never met,"},{"time":269843,"text":"but calling the tiniest slice of the one percent?"},{"time":273311,"text":"As anyone would, as they do this,"},{"time":275679,"text":"they develop a sixth sense, a constant awareness"},{"time":279527,"text":"about how what they do might affect their ability to raise money."},{"time":282867,"text":"They become, in the words of \"The X-Files,\""},{"time":284283,"text":"shape-shifters, as they constantly adjust their views"},{"time":287727,"text":"in light of what they know will help them to raise money,"},{"time":290589,"text":"not on issues one to 10,"},{"time":292158,"text":"but on issues 11 to 1,000."},{"time":295253,"text":"Leslie Byrne, a Democrat from Virginia,"},{"time":296967,"text":"describes that when she went to Congress,"},{"time":298577,"text":"she was told by a colleague, \"Always lean to the green.\""},{"time":302502,"text":"Then to clarify, she went on,"},{"time":304138,"text":"\"He was not an environmentalist.\" (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":308832,"text":"So here too we have a democracy,"},{"time":310912,"text":"a democracy dependent upon the funders"},{"time":312927,"text":"and dependent upon the people,"},{"time":314714,"text":"competing dependencies,"},{"time":316851,"text":"possibly conflicting dependencies"},{"time":318870,"text":"depending upon who the funders are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322481,"text":"Okay, the United States is Lesterland, point number one."},{"time":325242,"text":"Here's point number two."},{"time":327253,"text":"The United States is worse than Lesterland,"},{"time":330035,"text":"worse than Lesterland because you can imagine in Lesterland"},{"time":332916,"text":"if we Lesters got a letter from the government that said,"},{"time":335268,"text":"\"Hey, you get to pick who gets to run in the general election,\""},{"time":338532,"text":"we would think maybe of a kind of aristocracy of Lesters."},{"time":342683,"text":"You know, there are Lesters from every part of social society."},{"time":344972,"text":"There are rich Lesters, poor Lesters, black Lesters, white Lesters,"},{"time":347620,"text":"not many women Lesters, but put that to the side for one second."},{"time":350348,"text":"We have Lesters from everywhere. We could think,"},{"time":352476,"text":"\"What could we do to make Lesterland better?\""},{"time":355484,"text":"It's at least possible the Lesters would act for the good of Lesterland."},{"time":360259,"text":"But in our land, in this land, in USA-land,"},{"time":363502,"text":"there are certainly some sweet Lesters out there,"},{"time":366125,"text":"many of them in this room here today,"},{"time":368097,"text":"but the vast majority of Lesters act for the Lesters,"},{"time":372581,"text":"because the shifting coalitions that are comprising the .05 percent"},{"time":376969,"text":"are not comprising it for the public interest."},{"time":379094,"text":"It's for their private interest. In this sense, the USA is worse than Lesterland."}]},{"cues":[{"time":383486,"text":"And finally, point number three:"},{"time":385907,"text":"Whatever one wants to say about Lesterland,"},{"time":388854,"text":"against the background of its history, its traditions,"},{"time":391158,"text":"in our land, in USA-land, Lesterland is a corruption,"},{"time":396101,"text":"a corruption."},{"time":397574,"text":"Now, by corruption I don't mean brown paper bag cash"},{"time":401597,"text":"secreted among members of Congress."},{"time":403465,"text":"I don't mean Rod Blagojevich sense of corruption."},{"time":406525,"text":"I don't mean any criminal act."},{"time":408430,"text":"The corruption I'm talking about is perfectly legal."},{"time":411821,"text":"It's a corruption relative to the framers' baseline for this republic."},{"time":416874,"text":"The framers gave us what they called a republic,"},{"time":420369,"text":"but by a republic they meant a representative democracy,"},{"time":424551,"text":"and by a representative democracy, they meant a government,"},{"time":427738,"text":"as Madison put it in Federalist 52, that would have a branch"},{"time":430717,"text":"that would be dependent upon the people alone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435662,"text":"So here's the model of government."},{"time":436677,"text":"They have the people and the government"},{"time":439282,"text":"with this exclusive dependency,"},{"time":441715,"text":"but the problem here is that Congress has evolved a different dependence,"},{"time":445818,"text":"no longer a dependence upon the people alone,"},{"time":448491,"text":"increasingly a dependence upon the funders."},{"time":450920,"text":"Now this is a dependence too,"},{"time":454058,"text":"but it's different and conflicting from a dependence upon the people alone"},{"time":457922,"text":"so long as the funders are not the people."},{"time":462228,"text":"This is a corruption."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464491,"text":"Now, there's good news and bad news about this corruption."},{"time":466991,"text":"One bit of good news is that it's bipartisan,"},{"time":469355,"text":"equal-opportunity corruption."},{"time":471525,"text":"It blocks the left on a whole range of issues that we on the left really care about."},{"time":476178,"text":"It blocks the right too, as it makes"},{"time":478650,"text":"principled arguments of the right increasingly impossible."},{"time":482570,"text":"So the right wants smaller government."},{"time":484762,"text":"When Al Gore was Vice President, his team had an idea"},{"time":487458,"text":"for deregulating a significant portion of the telecommunications industry."},{"time":491370,"text":"The chief policy man took this idea to Capitol Hill,"},{"time":494050,"text":"and as he reported back to me,"},{"time":496083,"text":"the response was, \"Hell no!"},{"time":498282,"text":"If we deregulate these guys,"},{"time":500058,"text":"how are we going to raise money from them?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":503816,"text":"This is a system that's designed to save the status quo,"},{"time":507623,"text":"including the status quo of big and invasive government."},{"time":511256,"text":"It works against the left and the right,"},{"time":513706,"text":"and that, you might say, is good news."}]},{"cues":[{"time":515252,"text":"But here's the bad news."},{"time":517041,"text":"It's a pathological, democracy-destroying corruption,"},{"time":520944,"text":"because in any system"},{"time":523200,"text":"where the members are dependent upon"},{"time":525100,"text":"the tiniest fraction of us for their election,"},{"time":528272,"text":"that means the tiniest number of us,"},{"time":531064,"text":"the tiniest, tiniest number of us,"},{"time":533344,"text":"can block reform."},{"time":535055,"text":"I know that should have been, like, a rock or something."},{"time":537953,"text":"I can only find cheese. I'm sorry. So there it is."},{"time":539990,"text":"Block reform."}]},{"cues":[{"time":542384,"text":"Because there is an economy here, an economy of influence,"},{"time":546360,"text":"an economy with lobbyists at the center"},{"time":548914,"text":"which feeds on polarization."},{"time":551568,"text":"It feeds on dysfunction."},{"time":553417,"text":"The worse that it is for us,"},{"time":556056,"text":"the better that it is for this fundraising."}]},{"cues":[{"time":559992,"text":"Henry David Thoreau: \"There are a thousand hacking"},{"time":563104,"text":"at the branches of evil to one who is striking at the root.\""},{"time":567976,"text":"This is the root."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571369,"text":"Okay, now, every single one of you knows this."},{"time":575512,"text":"You couldn't be here if you didn't know this, yet you ignore it."},{"time":579141,"text":"You ignore it. This is an impossible problem."},{"time":582725,"text":"You focus on the possible problems,"},{"time":585273,"text":"like eradicating polio from the world,"},{"time":588536,"text":"or taking an image of every single street across the globe,"},{"time":591670,"text":"or building the first real universal translator,"},{"time":594976,"text":"or building a fusion factory in your garage."},{"time":598578,"text":"These are the manageable problems, so you ignore —"},{"time":601496,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause) —"},{"time":607128,"text":"so you ignore this corruption."}]},{"cues":[{"time":609577,"text":"But we cannot ignore this corruption anymore."},{"time":615047,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":618152,"text":"We need a government that works."},{"time":621735,"text":"And not works for the left or the right,"},{"time":624600,"text":"but works for the left and the right,"},{"time":627064,"text":"the citizens of the left and right,"},{"time":629096,"text":"because there is no sensible reform possible"},{"time":632688,"text":"until we end this corruption."},{"time":635217,"text":"So I want you to take hold, to grab the issue you care the most about."},{"time":639402,"text":"Climate change is mine, but it might be financial reform"},{"time":641962,"text":"or a simpler tax system or inequality."},{"time":644330,"text":"Grab that issue, sit it down in front of you,"},{"time":646518,"text":"look straight in its eyes, and tell it there is no Christmas this year."},{"time":650359,"text":"There will never be a Christmas."},{"time":652185,"text":"We will never get your issue solved"},{"time":654897,"text":"until we fix this issue first."},{"time":657863,"text":"So it's not that mine is the most important issue. It's not."},{"time":661193,"text":"Yours is the most important issue, but mine is the first issue,"},{"time":665369,"text":"the issue we have to solve before we get to fix"},{"time":668090,"text":"the issues you care about."},{"time":670063,"text":"No sensible reform, and we cannot afford"},{"time":673361,"text":"a world, a future, with no sensible reform."}]},{"cues":[{"time":677282,"text":"Okay. So how do we do it?"},{"time":680153,"text":"Turns out, the analytics here are easy, simple."},{"time":683641,"text":"If the problem is members spending an extraordinary"},{"time":686491,"text":"amount of time fundraising from the tiniest slice of America,"},{"time":689651,"text":"the solution is to have them spend less time fundraising"},{"time":693911,"text":"but fundraise from a wider slice of Americans,"},{"time":696579,"text":"to spread it out,"},{"time":697752,"text":"to spread the funder influence so that we restore the idea"},{"time":701033,"text":"of dependence upon the people alone."},{"time":704225,"text":"And to do this does not require a constitutional amendment,"},{"time":707655,"text":"changing the First Amendment."},{"time":708914,"text":"To do this would require a single statute,"},{"time":712273,"text":"a statute establishing what we think of"},{"time":714465,"text":"as small dollar funded elections,"},{"time":717161,"text":"a statute of citizen-funded campaigns,"},{"time":719369,"text":"and there's any number of these proposals out there:"},{"time":721465,"text":"Fair Elections Now Act,"},{"time":722911,"text":"the American Anti-Corruption Act,"},{"time":725337,"text":"an idea in my book that I call the Grant and Franklin Project"},{"time":728427,"text":"to give vouchers to people to fund elections,"},{"time":730761,"text":"an idea of John Sarbanes called the Grassroots Democracy Act."},{"time":733956,"text":"Each of these would fix this corruption"},{"time":738060,"text":"by spreading out the influence of funders to all of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":742409,"text":"The analytics are easy here."},{"time":745067,"text":"It's the politics that's hard, indeed impossibly hard,"},{"time":750580,"text":"because this reform would shrink K Street,"},{"time":756939,"text":"and Capitol Hill, as Congressman Jim Cooper,"},{"time":761799,"text":"a Democrat from Tennessee, put it,"},{"time":764779,"text":"has become a farm league for K Street, a farm league for K Street."},{"time":769599,"text":"Members and staffers and bureaucrats have"},{"time":771564,"text":"an increasingly common business model in their head,"},{"time":773775,"text":"a business model focused on their life after government,"},{"time":776843,"text":"their life as lobbyists."},{"time":779164,"text":"Fifty percent of the Senate between 1998 and 2004"},{"time":782710,"text":"left to become lobbyists, 42 percent of the House."},{"time":785368,"text":"Those numbers have only gone up,"},{"time":786844,"text":"and as United Republic calculated last April,"},{"time":789190,"text":"the average increase in salary for those who they tracked"},{"time":792403,"text":"was 1,452 percent."},{"time":797765,"text":"So it's fair to ask, how is it possible for them to change this?"},{"time":804131,"text":"Now I get this skepticism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":808195,"text":"I get this cynicism. I get this sense of impossibility."},{"time":813131,"text":"But I don't buy it."},{"time":815459,"text":"This is a solvable issue."},{"time":819307,"text":"If you think about the issues our parents tried to solve"},{"time":822467,"text":"in the 20th century,"},{"time":824306,"text":"issues like racism, or sexism,"},{"time":827587,"text":"or the issue that we've been fighting in this century, homophobia,"},{"time":830700,"text":"those are hard issues."},{"time":833187,"text":"You don't wake up one day no longer a racist."},{"time":836107,"text":"It takes generations to tear that intuition, that DNA,"},{"time":840418,"text":"out of the soul of a people."},{"time":842863,"text":"But this is a problem of just incentives, just incentives."},{"time":846108,"text":"Change the incentives, and the behavior changes,"},{"time":848651,"text":"and the states that have adopted small dollar funded systems"},{"time":851338,"text":"have seen overnight a change in the practice."},{"time":854468,"text":"When Connecticut adopted this system,"},{"time":856449,"text":"in the very first year, 78 percent of elected representatives"},{"time":860639,"text":"gave up large contributions and took small contributions only."},{"time":864886,"text":"It's solvable,"},{"time":866865,"text":"not by being a Democrat,"},{"time":869675,"text":"not by being a Republican."},{"time":871470,"text":"It's solvable by being citizens, by being citizens,"},{"time":875122,"text":"by being TEDizens."},{"time":878105,"text":"Because if you want to kickstart reform,"},{"time":882442,"text":"look, I could kickstart reform"},{"time":885893,"text":"at half the price of fixing energy policy,"},{"time":889481,"text":"I could give you back a republic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":892263,"text":"Okay. But even if you're not yet with me,"},{"time":895907,"text":"even if you believe this is impossible,"},{"time":899492,"text":"what the five years since I spoke at TED has taught me"},{"time":902929,"text":"as I've spoken about this issue again and again is,"},{"time":905527,"text":"even if you think it's impossible, that is irrelevant."},{"time":909353,"text":"Irrelevant."},{"time":911341,"text":"I spoke at Dartmouth once, and a woman stood up after I spoke,"},{"time":914909,"text":"I write in my book, and she said to me,"},{"time":916752,"text":"\"Professor, you've convinced me this is hopeless. Hopeless."},{"time":922445,"text":"There's nothing we can do.\""},{"time":925295,"text":"When she said that, I scrambled."},{"time":927220,"text":"I tried to think, \"How do I respond to that hopelessness?"},{"time":929362,"text":"What is that sense of hopelessness?\""},{"time":931025,"text":"And what hit me was an image of my six-year-old son."},{"time":935887,"text":"And I imagined a doctor coming to me and saying,"},{"time":939072,"text":"\"Your son has terminal brain cancer, and there's nothing you can do."},{"time":946381,"text":"Nothing you can do.\""},{"time":948635,"text":"So would I do nothing?"},{"time":951730,"text":"Would I just sit there? Accept it? Okay, nothing I can do?"},{"time":954102,"text":"I'm going off to build Google Glass."},{"time":957925,"text":"Of course not. I would do everything I could,"},{"time":961571,"text":"and I would do everything I could because this is what love means,"},{"time":965151,"text":"that the odds are irrelevant and that you do"},{"time":967467,"text":"whatever the hell you can, the odds be damned."},{"time":971046,"text":"And then I saw the obvious link, because even we liberals"},{"time":974887,"text":"love this country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":977146,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":980119,"text":"And so when the pundits and the politicians"},{"time":982379,"text":"say that change is impossible,"},{"time":984689,"text":"what this love of country says back is,"},{"time":987751,"text":"\"That's just irrelevant.\""},{"time":990487,"text":"We lose something dear,"},{"time":992527,"text":"something everyone in this room loves and cherishes,"},{"time":995734,"text":"if we lose this republic, and so we act"},{"time":999682,"text":"with everything we can to prove these pundits wrong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1004976,"text":"So here's my question:"},{"time":1007412,"text":"Do you have that love?"},{"time":1012023,"text":"Do you have that love?"},{"time":1014848,"text":"Because if you do,"},{"time":1016531,"text":"then what the hell are you, what are the hell are we doing?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1021920,"text":"When Ben Franklin was carried from the constitutional convention"},{"time":1026460,"text":"in September of 1787, he was stopped in the street by a woman who said,"},{"time":1030466,"text":"\"Mr. Franklin, what have you wrought?\""},{"time":1033924,"text":"Franklin said, \"A republic, madam, if you can keep it.\""},{"time":1041685,"text":"A republic. A representative democracy."},{"time":1046584,"text":"A government dependent upon the people alone."},{"time":1053793,"text":"We have lost that republic."},{"time":1058378,"text":"All of us have to act to get it back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1062726,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1064370,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1070423,"text":"Thank you. Thank you. Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}